000002C *> 28/10/16 vbc - .00  Made a copybook to make it easier for maintenance
000003C *>                     All msgs start with SY00.
000004C *>                     Rem out all refs to ACAS_IRS as all files in same dir
000005C *>                     after RDB conv and using ACAS system param file.
000006C *> 14/03/18 vbc - .01  Accept more than one param in case cron running to force a
000007C *>                     program to be run via the menu programs without user intervention.
000008C *>                     This at least for running st020 and st040.
000009C *>                     There may well be more.
000010C *> 21/04/18 vbc - .02  Added xl150 called by sales and purchase.
000011C *>                     New creates ACAS-Path with path/
000012C *> 29/04/18 vbc - .03  Added extra test and display if error in program-get-args.
000013C *> 24/05/18 vbc - .04  Changed method of getting program command line params as existing
000014C *>                     is not working correctly.
000015C *> 31/05/23 vbc - .05  USe TRIM when getting ACAS-LEDGER content.
000016C *>
000017C  zz010-Get-Env-Set-Files section.
000018C *>******************************
000019C *>
000020C      accept   ACAS_LEDGERS from Environment "ACAS_LEDGERS".
000021C      accept   ACAS_BIN     from Environment "ACAS_BIN".
000022C *>
000023C      if       ACAS_LEDGERS (1:1) = spaces
000024C            or ACAS_BIN (1:1) = spaces
000025C               display SY009   at 0505 with erase eos highlight
000026C               display SY008   at 1210 with           foreground-color 3 highlight
000027C               accept ws-reply at 1243
000028C               stop run
000029C      end-if
000030C      if       ACAS_LEDGERS (1:1) = "\" or "/"          *> Its Windows or Linux/Unix/OSX
000031C               move ACAS_LEDGERS (1:1) to OS-Delimiter      *> "  (4 editor kate)
000032C      end-if.
000033C *>
000034C  zz010-GESF-Exit.
000035C      exit     section.
000036C *>
000037C  zz020-Get-Program-Args      section.
000038C *>**********************************
000039C *>
